  {
    "client_msg_id": "ce3c935a-e04a-48ff-9ad0-fb436c47c19d",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "The way g9 (and Carbide) use optimization to recalculate changes to the input parameters is clever. I don’t know if there are other tools that do something similar. Adding something like that to existing Javascript libraries, say, d3.js, would be neat, but would require quite a lot of tooling. With something like p5.js or Open/WebGL, might not be that difficult (since they use context in the same way as g9 does).",
